channel.title: Client's Native Methods
channel.description:
For the latest client. Might be useful. Client: http://rafb.net/p/RQ9Ne867.html Loader: http://rafb.net/p/I3EZz041.html
Point of clarification: these are not native method calls but calls to the java api which i regard as "native". These calls have the possibility of making any bot you make detectable. The idea is you look at these and make sure that a call to these methods will not affect you.

item.title: Client's Native Methods
item.dc:creator: @pplsuqbawlz pplsuqbawlz
item.description:
@pplsuqbawlz wrote:

Precisely frank_.

And no he didn’t search for a name like that :-p; what I hope he did is made a repository of teh client jar, then ran through every constant in each class and did a check on the default runtime jar to see if it existed there… If it does, I hope he then added it to an ArrayList and finally converted it to an array which he then dumped.

And it’s incredibly useful, and incredibly… dull; It does give us many points of access to hack-up the client. But it also gives us a basis for say… if we wanted to make runescape run in our own homebrew runtime (giving us full access to the client undetectably) and also increasing runtime efficiency. No?

Read full topic
